@startuml recall-consolidate-lifecycle
' Sequence: one vector's journey across the seam.
' client write -> Recall (lsn=k, immediately queryable) -> query union serves
' it FROM Recall -> consolidation builds a shard, commits watermark=N>=k,
' grace-trims -> query union now serves it FROM Consolidate -> the Recall row
' is eventually trimmed once its shard is >= 2 generations old.

title One vector's journey: Recall -> (consolidation) -> Consolidate (RB_RECALL on)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "client" as client
participant "cp\n(Control Plane)" as cp
participant "query_dp\n(union + merge)" as dp
database "Recall\n(pgvector)" as recall
participant "index_builder\n(consolidate)" as builder
database "shard_catalog\n(consolidated_lsn)" as catalog
collections "Consolidate\n(S3 shards)" as os

== t0: write -- vector V lands in Recall ==

client -> cp : POST /vectors {id=V, values}
cp -> recall : nextval(lsn_seq) -> lsn = k;\nUPSERT (V, .., lsn=k, deleted=false)
activate recall
recall --> cp : durable
deactivate recall
cp --> client : 200 OK
note over recall #E9F7E9
  V now lives at lsn=k, with k > consolidated_lsn(W).
  It is in the RECALL set and immediately queryable.
end note

== t1: query union serves V FROM Recall ==

client -> dp : POST /query {vector ~ V}
activate dp
dp -> catalog : resolve latest shard S, read consolidated_lsn(S) = W   (W < k)
dp -> os : FAISS search S  (V not here yet)
dp -> recall : exact: NOT deleted, lsn > W  -> matches V (lsn=k)
dp -> dp : square pgvector L2 -> L2^2, recall-wins dedup, sort, top_k
dp --> client : matches include V  [served from RECALL]
deactivate dp

== t2: consolidation -- snap V into a shard, advance watermark ==

builder -> recall : snapshot lsn <= N   (N >= k, so V is in the snapshot)
activate builder
builder -> os : build + write new shard containing V + sidecar
builder -> catalog : COMMIT consolidated_lsn = N\n(commit the shard BEFORE trimming Recall)
note over catalog #LightYellow
  Watermark snaps W -> N (N >= k).
  Now lsn=k is <= consolidated_lsn -> V belongs to CONSOLIDATE.
end note
builder -> recall : grace-bounded TRIM lsn <= 2nd-newest wm (= W, not N)\n(only after commit; grace buffer keeps (W,N] one extra generation)\n-- V (lsn=k in (W,N]) is KEPT for now
deactivate builder

== t3: query union now serves V FROM Consolidate ==

client -> dp : POST /query {vector ~ V}
activate dp
dp -> catalog : resolve latest shard S' (the new one), consolidated_lsn(S') = N
dp -> os : FAISS search S'  -> matches V (now in the shard)
dp -> recall : exact: lsn > N  -> V (lsn=k) NOT returned (k <= N) -> no duplicate
dp -> dp : merge -> single copy of V
dp --> client : matches include V  [served from CONSOLIDATE]
deactivate dp
note over recall, os #E7F3FD
  V's Recall row still physically exists in (W, N] as a grace
  buffer (kept one extra generation), but the union excludes it
  (lsn > N is false). No loss, no duplicate.
end note

== t4: V's Recall row is eventually trimmed ==

builder -> recall : later consolidation: shard S' is now >= 2 gens old\n-> trim reclaims lsn <= N, hard-deleting V's Recall row
note over recall #FDF3E7
  V now lives ONLY in the Consolidate tier.
  Idle datasets drain Recall to 0 -> queries skip pgvector.
end note

@enduml
